{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"320d2194-7377-4f31-95ef-e7e0ce8d8e51","content":"The template has a solid foundation but has a few issues to fix before publishing:\n\n**🔴 Bug — `choices` format is wrong** (lines 18-21): Must be an array of objects, not a keyed object:\n```json\n\"choices\": [\n  { \"choice\": \"net8.0\", \"description\": \".NET 8\" },\n  { \"choice\": \"net9.0\", \"description\": \".NET 9\" }\n]\n```\n\n**🔴 Missing `replaces` on `Framework` symbol**: Without it, the selected framework value won't be substituted into output files (e.g., `<TargetFramework>` in `.csproj`). Add `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"` to the symbol.\n\n**🟡 Missing `$schema`**: Recommended for editor validation:\n```json\n\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"\n```\n\n**🟡 Missing `groupIdentity`**: Recommended when publishing to NuGet for template discoverability/versioning (e.g., `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi\"`).\n\n**✅ Good**: `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `sourceName`, `author`, `classifications`, and `tags` all look correct.\n\nWant me to apply these fixes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b324e158-1aa8-4e0c-8068-f111ca117e65","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nIssues I can identify:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but strongly recommended for tooling/validation. The standard value is `http://json.schemastore.org/template`.\n\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet packages, especially if you plan to have multiple related templates.\n\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Not required but useful for versioning.\n\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Not required, but common.\n\n\nThe core metadata fields like `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, and `sourceName` all look good, and you've got `author`, `classifications`, and `tags` properly set. However, I'm noticing an issue with the `Framework` symbol in the `symbols` section — it's using a `choices` object structure, but the template schema expects an array of choice objects instead. not an array of objects with `choice` and `description` properties. There's also a missing `replaces` property on the `Framework` symbol — it should specify what text gets substituted in the template files, like `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"` to update the target framework in the .csproj file. So far I've identified a schema validation issue and two functional problems with the parameter definitions.","outputTokens":1093,"requestId":"FC08:17D0EF:C7A68E:E8B140:69FE86E0"},"id":"fbce5756-a507-43e6-a03b-bb21d6ccf636","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:59:34.111Z","parentId":"d0adcbb4-3b58-4842-a125-4502ef61b2b3"}
